      "id": "PopularPost6917",
      "post_content": "I remember seeing this card back in the day, in decks that specialized in counterspells. It allowed the control player to sink their open mana into something at the end of their opponent's turn, if they didn't counter anything that turn. These days, however, there are far more powerful ways of drawing cards on opponents' turns.",
